('b0000001-0000-4000-8000-002000010000','Jonas Brückner','+49 152 9043 7718','Fukuoka','group','2026-08-08','14:30','3D2N',3,'We three shared a cramped studio through architecture school in Leipzig and always sketched buildings we swore we''d visit. Kyushu''s mix of volcanic onsen towns and Nagasaki''s layered history is exactly the kind of place we used to argue about over cheap wine at 2am. We want one slow, beautiful kaiseki evening in a Yufuin ryokan as our splurge. All three of us are vegetarian — please make sure the ryokan kaiseki can be done without fish or dashi.','unassigned',7300,false,NULL,34000,32000,
 '{"seed_batch":"jp-01","market":"japan","person_id":"0020","unit_order":1,"unit_total":4,"trip_start_date":"2026-08-08","trip_end_date":"2026-08-14","trip_total_duration":"7D6N","origin_country":"Germany","origin_city":"Leipzig","ages":[37,39,36],"languages":["German","English (fluent)"],"occasion":"Three architecture-school friends taking their first trip together since graduating","budget_tier":"mid_range","daily_spend_per_pax_eur":34000,"hotel_budget_per_night_eur":96000,"hotel_budget_per_night_pax_eur":32000,"pace":"active","splurge_willingness":"one_two_splurges","dietary_restrictions":"vegetarian","mobility":"Fully mobile, keen walkers who''ll happily wander a city all day on foot","interests":["architecture","history","onsen","hidden_gems","art_museums"],"must_avoid":"Cookie-cutter chain hotels and rushed itineraries — we''d rather see one place properly than tick boxes","previous_visits_japan":"first_time","booking_authority":"mix","accommodation_preference":"Design-conscious small ryokan or boutique stays; one traditional tatami onsen ryokan in Yufuin is a must. Three single rooms or one large room with separate futons"}'::jsonb),
